  convention (quoted title/description frontmatter, permalink: /slug/ trailing slash, single H1,
  top+bottom CTA to /mail-merge-for-gmail-and-sheets/, internal links to existing pages). No GPT-for-Sheets
  CTA leakage in page bodies (0 references in source; the 9 matches in generated HTML are the shared
  site nav/footer only). Saleshandy comparison page is independent/unaffiliated, factual workflow-fit
  framing ("if you want a Sheets-native workflow", no "better than"), no hard-coded competitor pricing
  ("as of 2026, check vendor"). Excel-migration page accurately states Gmail can't read .xlsx directly and
  that Workspace native mail merge is plan-gated. Multi-account page frames splitting as legitimate
  organization within per-account limits (explicitly not quota evasion) with consent/CAN-SPAM/GDPR and
  warm-up cautions. Appointment-reminder page adds opt-out + HIPAA-type privacy caution and avoids
  exact no-show-reduction claims. Only the 4 new files were staged/committed (explicit git add); unrelated
  dirty files left UNTOUCHED: claude-for-sheets-alternative-google-sheets-ai.md (modified),
